1) REST APIs

https://restfulapi.net/  
A truly RESTful API looks like hypertext. Every addressable unit of information carries an address, 
either explicitly (e.g., link and id attributes) 
or implicitly (e.g., derived from the media type definition and representation structure).

https://www.edureka.co/blog/what-is-rest-api/


2)Microservices

https://microservices.io/

Microservices - also known as the microservice architecture - is an architectural style that structures an 
application as a collection of services that are

Highly maintainable and testable
Loosely coupled
Independently deployable
Organized around business capabilities
Owned by a small team




